Build instructions on OSX (ARM), using homebrew as the package manager

## Native build

```bash
brew install boost

./bootstrap
CPPFLAGS="-I/opt/homebrew/include" LDFLAGS="-L/opt/homebrew/lib" ./configure
make
```

Run `utils/eliottxt` as the app

## Emscripten build

```bash
brew install emscripten
brew install boost

./bootstrap
CPPFLAGS="-I/opt/homebrew/include -fexceptions" LDFLAGS="-L/opt/homebrew/lib" LIBS="-lnodefs.js -fexceptions" emconfigure ./configure
emmake make
```

Generate website full example code with dictionary preload file. Run from `utils` directory:

```bash
/opt/homebrew/Cellar/emscripten/5.0.2/libexec/em++  -g3 -O2 -Wall -Wextra  -L/opt/homebrew/lib -o eliottxt.html game_io.o eliottxt.o ../game/libgame.a ../dic/libdic.a -fexceptions -gsource-map --preload-file ../dictionaries
```
